Workflow Documentation

Workflow documentation explains complex system processes using clear steps, decision points, and system interactions. 
It helps in understanding how different components of CookSnap â€“ Smart Recipe Recommendation System Using Grocery Images work together in real-world usage scenarios.

Workflow 1: End-to-End Recipe Recommendation Workflow

The user opens the CookSnap application.

The user uploads an image of available groceries.

The system validates image format and system availability.

The image is processed by the image recognition module.

Ingredients are detected from the uploaded image.

The system matches detected ingredients with the recipe database.

Suitable recipes are generated based on ingredient availability.

The recommended recipes are displayed to the user.

The user selects a recipe to view detailed cooking instructions.

This workflow ensures efficient meal planning, reduces food wastage, and provides a smooth user experience.

Workflow 2: Administrative System Monitoring Workflow

The admin logs into the CookSnap system using valid credentials.

The system authenticates the admin and grants dashboard access.

The admin views system usage statistics and activity data.

The admin manages recipe data or user access if required.

The system collects relevant usage information.

The report module generates system performance reports.

The admin reviews reports to analyze system usage and performance.

This workflow supports effective system monitoring, maintenance, and data-driven decision making.
